Manchester United welcome Liverpool in the Super Sunday clash this weekend. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s men went into the international break in 12th place, two places above the relegation zone. The Reds however are top of the table and still boast of a 100% record in the league. Kick off is 4.30pm West African time. Sunday, October 20
